com.sap.spe.pricing.transactiondata

Interface IDocumentBase

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDocument, ISPCDocument

    public interface IDocumentBase
    This interface should be implemented by the (sales order) document/header and is used for callbacks of the pricing engine. It provides information of the (sales order) document which is needed for pricing.

    • Method Detail

      • getId

        java.lang.String getId()
        Returns:
        an Id which is used to save the pricing document to the local database. The id should have less or equal 10 digits. (R/3-field: KONV-KNUMV)

      • getLocalCurrency

        ICurrencyUnit getLocalCurrency()
        Returns:
        the name of the local(house) currency of the (sales) document. (R/3-field: KOMK-HWAER)

      • getDocumentCurrency

        ICurrencyUnit getDocumentCurrency()
        Returns:
        the name of the document currency of the (sales) document. All condition values are calculated in this currency.(R/3-field: KOMK-WAERK)

      • getPricingProcedure

        IPricingProcedure getPricingProcedure()
        Returns:
        the name of the pricing procedure which is then used by the pricing engine to search for condition records. (R/3-field: KOMK-KALSM)

      • getUsage

        java.lang.String getUsage()
        Returns:
        the usage of the external document.

      • getApplication

        java.lang.String getApplication()
        Returns:
        the application of the external document. For a sales order the application is "V". (R/3-field: KOMK-KAPPL)

      • getEditMode

        char getEditMode()
        Returns:
        the edit mode of the (sales) document. The edit mode contains information e.g. about whether the document is editable or not.

      • isPartialProcessing

        boolean isPartialProcessing()
        Returns:
        the partial processing flag of the (sales) document. The partial processing flag contains information about if all documents lineitems are processed or not.

      • getAuthorityForDisplay

        int getAuthorityForDisplay()
        Returns:
        the authority level the user has to display this document's conditions.

      • getAuthorityForEdit

        int getAuthorityForEdit()
        Returns:
        the authority level the user has to edit this document's conditions.

      • isOnlySpecifiedUsage

        boolean isOnlySpecifiedUsage()
        Returns:
        the flag whether only condition records of the given usage should be accessed.

      • isKeepingZeroPricesActive

        boolean isKeepingZeroPricesActive()
        Returns:
        the flag if prices with the rate 0 are set to inactive.

      • isPerformingTrace

        boolean isPerformingTrace()
        Returns:
        the flag if a trace is performed or not.

      • getUnitToBeRoundedTo

        int getUnitToBeRoundedTo()
        Returns:
        the unit to be rounded, e.g. 5 for the so-called 5-Rappen-rounding in swisse. Should be 0 if no rounding should be performed. (R/3-field: T001R-REINH)

      • getItemBases

        IItemBase[] getItemBases()
        Returns:
        a vector of Iitems of the external (sales) document. This is needed if a pricing document should be loaded from the local database.

      • getBusinessObjectType

        java.lang.String getBusinessObjectType()
        Returns:
        the name of the related business object type. All available business object types are documented in the SAP Business Object Repository (BOR)

      • getExpiringCheckDate

        SAPDate getExpiringCheckDate()

      • getVarcondFieldname

        java.lang.String getVarcondFieldname()

        fielname of the variant condition field (usually "VARCOND")

      • isSimulation

        boolean isSimulation()

      • isLazyItemLoadMode

        boolean isLazyItemLoadMode()

      • isReturnDocument

        Returns:

        Returns:

      • isLeanDcoument

        boolean isLeanDcoument()
        to check whether this document is a 'lean document' or not. Lean document is used for interactive configuration in decoupled pricing and configuration scenario.
        Returns:
